President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Fred Joseph Federici III and Brenda M. Saiz as Judges on the United States District Court for the District of New Mexico. Fred Federici is currently serving as the First Assistant United States Attorney in the United States Attorney's Office for the District of New Mexico. He has 25 years of experience as a Federal Prosecutor and has held various supervisor positions. Brenda Saiz, on the other hand, is a Director at Rodey, Dickason, Sloan, Akin, & Robb, P.A., in Albuquerque, New Mexico. Her practice focuses on trial practice and complex civil litigation, and she serves as the Leader of the Products and General Liability Practice Group. She is also an adjunct professor at the University of New Mexico School of Law, teaching Civil Procedure Drafting. Both nominees have strong legal backgrounds and qualifications for their respective positions.